Using the app on my Note 8. The reasons why I have requested a refund are threefold. 1). A message popped up saying I had exceeded my daily data limit within the app screen itself. Then moments later it cleared and my data came back! 2). When you enlarge the map and unlock what you are tracking the map moves fine from east/west but trying to go north/south is very hit and miss and the map just seems to get stuck and won't move sometimes. 3). When you have the map enlarged trying to switch between the object browser and the radar screens was met with frustration. Its a great app but sorry I'm not prepared to be frustrated at basic UI stuff for nearly ¬£2.
replyContent:
Sorry, for the short answers space is very limited. Email me support@issdetector.com for a better explanation and the refund.
1) Very rare condition at our Iridium data provider. You should not see this message.
2) Probably a device specific issue, will test on a Samsung.
3) Hit the back or the collapse button (bottom right) to get normal operation
